quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to break out of the loop after the number 5 is printed to the screen.
[!raw!]
for ($i=0;$i<=50;$i++)  {
  echo $i;
  if ($i=={0}) {
    {1};
  }
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The break Statement[/h1]

As discussed in the previous lesson, the [b]break [/b]statement is used to break out of the [b]switch [/b]when a case is matched.
If the break is absent, the code keeps running. For example:[code format="php" codeId="485"]$x=1;
switch ($x) {
  case 1:
    echo "One";
  case 2:
    echo "Two";
  case 3:
    echo "Three";
  default:
    echo "No match";
}

//Outputs "OneTwoThreeNo match"[/code]
Break can also be used to halt the execution of [b]for[/b], [b]foreach[/b], [b]while[/b], [b]do-while[/b] structures.
[note]The [b]break[/b] statement ends the current [b]for[/b], [b]foreach[/b], [b]while[/b], [b]do-while[/b] or [b]switch[/b] and continues to run the program on the line coming up after the loop. 
A [b]break[/b] statement in the outer part of a program (e.g., not in a control loop) will stop the script. [/note]
